item.title: [HIVE-19602] Refactor inplace progress code in Hive-on-spark progress monitor to use ProgressMonitor instance
item.description:
We can refactor the HOS inplace progress monitor code (SparkJobMonitor#printStatusInPlace) to use InplaceUpdate#render.

We can create an instance of ProgressMonitor and use it to show the progress.

This would be similar to :

https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/0b6bea89f74b607299ad944b37e4b62c711aaa69/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/exec/tez/monitoring/RenderStrategy.java#L181
item.summary: Refactor inplace progress code in Hive-on-spark progress monitor to use ProgressMonitor instance

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
Idea is to create a ProgressMonitor instance in SparkJobMonitor#printStatusInPlace and display it using InplaceUpdate#render.

This would help in HIVE-19176 as here we need to pass an instance of ProgressMonitor in the response to beeline, so we can maintain uniform format in both cases.

stakiar can you validate if this is a reasonable change.

LGTM +1

lirui might be interested in taking a look too, since he wrote most of this logic in HIVE-15039

stakiar Thanks for the review. I actually made a change in the patch. Can you please take a look at that.

Also submitting the patch for pre-commit tests.
Updated patch looks good
Thanks for pinging me. +1 pending test
